<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
  <meta charset="UTF-8" />
  <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0" />
  <title>Privacy Policy - Inzaar</title>
  <meta name="description" content="Privacy Policy for the Inzaar mobile application." />
  <style>
    :root {
      --bg: #f7f8fb;
      --card: #ffffff;
      --text: #1f2937;
      --muted: #6b7280;
      --heading: #0f172a;
      --accent: #0f766e;
      --border: #e5e7eb;
      --link: #0b57d0;
    }

    * {
      box-sizing: border-box;
    }

    body {
      margin: 0;
      font-family: Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif;
      background: var(--bg);
      color: var(--text);
      line-height: 1.65;
    }

    .container {
      max-width: 900px;
      margin: 40px auto;
      padding: 0 20px;
    }

    .card {
      background: var(--card);
      border: 1px solid var(--border);
      border-radius: 16px;
      padding: 32px;
      box-shadow: 0 10px 30px rgba(0,0,0,0.04);
    }

    h1, h2, h3 {
      color: var(--heading);
      line-height: 1.25;
      margin-top: 0;
    }

    h1 {
      font-size: 2rem;
      margin-bottom: 8px;
    }

    h2 {
      font-size: 1.25rem;
      margin-top: 32px;
      margin-bottom: 12px;
      padding-bottom: 8px;
      border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border);
    }

    p, li {
      font-size: 1rem;
    }

    .meta {
      color: var(--muted);
      margin-bottom: 24px;
    }

    ul {
      padding-left: 22px;
    }

    a {
      color: var(--link);
      text-decoration: none;
    }

    a:hover {
      text-decoration: underline;
    }

    .footer {
      margin-top: 28px;
      color: var(--muted);
      font-size: 0.95rem;
    }

    .notice {
      background: #ecfeff;
      border: 1px solid #a5f3fc;
      color: #164e63;
      border-radius: 12px;
      padding: 14px 16px;
      margin: 20px 0;
    }

    @media (max-width: 640px) {
      .card {
        padding: 22px;
      }

      h1 {
        font-size: 1.65rem;
      }
    }
  </style>
</head>
<body>
  <main class="container">
    <section class="card">
      <h1>Privacy Policy</h1>
      <p class="meta"><strong>Effective date:</strong> March 16, 2026</p>

      <p>
        This Privacy Policy describes how the Inzaar mobile application ("Inzaar", "the App", "we", "our", or "us")
        handles information when you use the App.
      </p>

      <p>
        Inzaar provides Islamic educational and informational content. The App does not require users to create an
        account or log in to access its core features.
      </p>

      <div class="notice">
        By using the App, you agree to this Privacy Policy.
      </div>

      <h2>1. Information We Collect</h2>
      <p>
        We do not require account registration or login. However, certain information may be collected automatically
        by the App or by third-party services integrated into the App.
      </p>

      <h3>Information collected automatically</h3>
      <ul>
        <li>Device information, such as device model, operating system version, language, and general technical details</li>
        <li>App usage information, such as interactions, session information, and performance data</li>
        <li>IP address or approximate network-based location information</li>
        <li>Advertising identifiers, such as the Android Advertising ID, where available</li>
        <li>Crash logs, diagnostics, and error-related information</li>
        <li>Purchase status information needed to determine whether an active premium subscription exists</li>
      </ul>

      <h3>Information we do not directly collect</h3>
      <ul>
        <li>Your username and password, because the App does not provide account login</li>
        <li>Your payment card or banking details, because purchases are processed by Google Play, not by us directly</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>2. How We Use Information</h2>
      <p>We use information handled through the App for purposes such as:</p>
      <ul>
        <li>Providing and maintaining the App</li>
        <li>Showing ads to free users</li>
        <li>Processing and recognizing premium subscription status to remove ads for subscribed users</li>
        <li>Improving app performance, stability, and user experience</li>
        <li>Diagnosing crashes and fixing technical issues</li>
        <li>Preventing misuse, fraud, and security issues</li>
        <li>Complying with legal obligations</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>3. Advertising</h2>
      <p>
        The App may display advertisements to users who are not subscribed to the premium ad-free offering.
      </p>

      <p>
        Ads may be served by third-party advertising partners, such as Google AdMob or other ad networks we may use
        from time to time. These services may collect or receive information from your device, including advertising
        identifiers, IP address, device information, and ad interaction information, to provide, improve, measure,
        and personalize advertising where permitted by applicable law and your device or consent settings.
      </p>

      <p>
        If you purchase an active premium subscription, ads are removed from the App while that subscription remains active,
        subject to successful subscription recognition by the App and Google Play.
      </p>

      <h2>4. In-App Purchases and Subscriptions</h2>
      <p>
        The App offers an optional recurring subscription that removes ads. Subscriptions and payments are processed
        through Google Play Billing.
      </p>

      <ul>
        <li>We do not directly collect or store your full payment card or bank details</li>
        <li>Billing, renewal, cancellation, refunds, and payment processing are handled according to Google Play’s systems and policies</li>
        <li>We may receive limited transaction or entitlement information necessary to confirm whether your subscription is active</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>5. Third-Party Services</h2>
      <p>
        The App may use third-party services and SDKs to support app functionality, advertising, subscriptions,
        analytics, diagnostics, and security.
      </p>

      <p>Examples may include:</p>
      <ul>
        <li>Google Play Services</li>
        <li>Google Play Billing</li>
        <li>Google AdMob</li>
        <li>Firebase Analytics</li>
        <li>Firebase Crashlytics</li>
      </ul>

      <p>
        These third parties may process information in accordance with their own privacy policies and terms.
      </p>

      <h2>6. Data Sharing</h2>
      <p>
        We do not sell your personal information.
      </p>

      <p>
        We may share limited information with service providers, partners, and platform providers only as needed to:
      </p>
      <ul>
        <li>Serve advertisements</li>
        <li>Process subscriptions and verify purchases</li>
        <li>Operate, secure, maintain, and improve the App</li>
        <li>Comply with legal obligations, enforce our rights, or respond to lawful requests</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>7. Data Retention</h2>
      <p>
        We retain information only for as long as reasonably necessary for the purposes described in this Privacy Policy,
        including to maintain app functionality, meet legal obligations, resolve disputes, and enforce agreements.
      </p>

      <p>
        Retention periods may vary depending on the type of data and whether it is processed by us or by third-party
        service providers.
      </p>

      <h2>8. Security</h2>
      <p>
        We use reasonable administrative, technical, and organizational measures to protect information associated with
        the App. However, no method of electronic storage or transmission is completely secure, and we cannot guarantee
        absolute security.
      </p>

      <h2>9. Your Choices and Controls</h2>
      <ul>
        <li>You can stop using the App at any time</li>
        <li>You can manage or cancel your subscription through your Google Play account</li>
        <li>You may be able to reset or limit your advertising identifier through your device settings</li>
        <li>You may be able to control certain permissions and privacy settings from your Android device</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>10. Children's Privacy</h2>
      <p>
        The App is not directed to children under the age of 13 unless expressly stated otherwise on the app store listing.
        We do not knowingly collect personal information from children under 13.
      </p>

      <p>
        If you believe that a child under 13 has provided personal information through the App, please contact us and we
        will take appropriate steps to review and address the issue.
      </p>

      <h2>11. External Links</h2>
      <p>
        The App may contain links to external websites or services, including the Inzaar website or third-party pages.
        We are not responsible for the privacy practices of third-party websites or services.
      </p>

      <h2>12. International Processing</h2>
      <p>
        Depending on the services used in the App, information may be processed on servers located in countries other
        than your own. By using the App, you understand that information may be transferred to and processed in countries
        where data protection laws may differ from those in your jurisdiction.
      </p>

      <h2>13. Changes to This Privacy Policy</h2>
      <p>
        We may update this Privacy Policy from time to time. When we do, we will revise the effective date at the top
        of this page. Your continued use of the App after an updated policy becomes effective constitutes acceptance of
        the updated Privacy Policy.
      </p>

      <h2>14. Contact Us</h2>
      <p>
        If you have any questions, requests, or concerns about this Privacy Policy, you can contact us at:
      </p>

      <p>
        <strong>Inzaar</strong><br />
        Website: <a href="https://www.inzaar.org/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">https://www.inzaar.org/</a><br />
        Email: <a href="mailto:support@inzaar.org">support@inzaar.org</a>
      </p>

      <div class="footer">
        Last updated: March 16, 2026
      </div>
    </section>
  </main>
</body>
</html>
